history.text: Hello
Have you seen inception?
No, I have not.
Who is in it?
Leonardo DiCaprio. Do you like science fiction movies?
Oh he is a good actor.
I am not a huge science fiction fan though.
Do you generally watch movies with good ratings? Users rated this 8.1 out of 10.
Yes I do. That is a pretty high rating.
If I remember correctly that movie won several Oscars.
Do you pay attention to what the critics have to say about a movie?
Sometimes I do but sometimes I pay more attention to a movies trailer to see if it may interest me.
If you like DiCaprio you might like this movie. One critic said that it will draw you in with a love story that will appeal even to non-sci-fi fans.
A love story? That does sound interesting. I like more comedies and romance movies.
Who plays the love interest in the movie?
Great. Then I think this movie may be something that you would like. Ellen Page plays Ariadne a graduate student of architecture.
She is recruited to construct dreamscapes which are described as mazes.
Sounds interesting. I have never seen any movies with her in it before.
Maybe you would like some other cast members Joseph Gordon-Levitt plays Arthur who researches the missions and Tom Hardy plays Eames an associate of Cobb (DiCaprio).
Oh yea both of those guys are good actors.  What kind of Business do they do?

Cobb is a professional thief who specializes in conning secrets from his victims by infiltrating their dreams. Cobb's partner Arthur manages and researches the missions while Ellen Page plays a key part to the love story. She constructs these "dreamscapes".
So they are all working together?
Yes, Cobb and Arthur are known as "extractors".
They are using these secrets against people to conn them?

They 
perform corporate espionage using an experimental military technology to infiltrate the subconscious of their targets and extract valuable information from a shared dream world.
This isn't a movie where it all ends up being a dream is it?
I'd hate to give away too much of the plot. Especially if you plan on seeing it. I don't want to ruin the movie for you.
What else should I know about the movie?
Their target in "inception" is Saito who wants to break up an energy conglomerate of ailing competitor.
Saito wants Cobb to convince Fischer's son and heir, Robert to dissolve his fathers company.
There is nothing else I can say about it, without giving too much of the plot away.
So other people are in the same business?
I know I don't want you to give the plot away.
I am not 100% sure it is my type of movie except for the love story part.
Saito wants to test Cobb with a seemly impossible job. Planting an idea in a persons subconscious or "inception

uid2response.feedback: It doesn't seem like my type of movie. Sounds a little confusing. I am also worried it is one of those movies ends up being a dream.
